goods /ɡʊdz/

1. N-PLURAL Goods are things that are made to be sold. 商品 

例： Money can be exchanged for goods or services. 钱可以用来换取商品或服务。 

2. N-PLURAL Your goods are the things that you own and that can be moved. 私人财产; 动产 

例： You can give your unwanted goods to charity. 你可以把不需要的东西捐给慈善机构。

